metadata.title: Cessna 310
aws::graph::propositions: Cessna 310 and 320 Aircraft Models
310S is the original designation for the Cessna 320.
Cessna 320 Skyknight is an enlarged version of the 310F.
Cessna 320 Skyknight has six seats.
Cessna 320 Skyknight has a larger cabin.
Cessna 320 Skyknight has two turbocharged engines.
110 Cessna 320 Skyknight aircraft were built.
Cessna 320A Skyknight is the first model with canted fuel tanks.
Cessna 320A Skyknight has minor changes compared to the 320 Skyknight.
47 Cessna 320A Skyknight aircraft were built.
Cessna 320B Skyknight is the first model with nacelle baggage lockers.
Cessna 320B Skyknight has minor changes compared to the 320A Skyknight.
62 Cessna 320B Skyknight aircraft were built.
Cessna 320C Skyknight has a longer cabin.
Cessna 320C Skyknight has an optional seventh seat.
Cessna 320C Skyknight has minor changes compared to the 320B Skyknight.
73 Cessna 320C Skyknight aircraft were built.
Cessna 320D Executive Skyknight has reshaped rear windows.
Cessna 320D Executive Skyknight has 285 hp (213 kW) TSIO-520-B engines.
130 Cessna 320D Executive Skyknight aircraft were built.
Cessna 320E Executive Skyknight has a pointed nose.
Cessna 320E Executive Skyknight has a single piece windshield.
Cessna 320E Executive Skyknight has modified landing gear.
Cessna 320E Executive Skyknight has increased takeoff weight.
Cessna 320E Executive Skyknight has minor changes compared to the 320D Executive Skyknight.
110 Cessna 320E Executive Skyknight aircraft were built.
Cessna 320F Executive Skyknight has minor changes compared to the 320E Executive Skyknight.
45 Cessna 320F Executive Skyknight aircraft were built.

text:
310S
Original designation for the Cessna 320.
320 Skyknight
Enlarged version of the 310F with six seats, larger cabin and two turbocharged engines; 110 built.
320A Skyknight
First model with canted fuel tanks and minor changes; 47 built.
320B Skyknight
First model with nacelle baggage lockers, minor changes; 62 built.
320C Skyknight
Model with a longer cabin, optional seventh seat and minor changes; 73 built.
320D Executive Skyknight
Model with reshaped rear windows and 285 hp (213 kW) TSIO-520-B engines; 130 built.
320E Executive Skyknight
Model with pointed nose, single piece windshield, modified landing gear, increased takeoff weight and minor changes; 110 built.
320F Executive Skyknight
Model with minor changes compared to 320E; 45 built.
